com.fgonzalesv.assignment6

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.Graph
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>

    public class Graph
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
    A Graph class that implements the GraphInterface given you. For Graph, V is the vertex type (a Town), E is the edge type (a Road). The graph is stored using an adjacent matrix or an adjacency list.
    Author:
    Fernando Gonzales-Vigil

      • addEdge

        public Road addEdge(Town sourceVertex,
                    Town destinationVertex,
                    int distance,
                    java.lang.String description)
             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException,
                    java.lang.NullPointerException
        Creates a new road in this graph, going from the source town to the target town, and returns the created road. The source and target towns must already be contained in this graph. If they are not found in graph IllegalArgumentException is thrown.
        Specified by:
        addEdge in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
        Parameters:
        sourceVertex - - source town of the road.
        destinationVertex - - target town of the road.
        distance - - distance of the road
        description - - description for road
        Returns:
        The newly created road if added to the graph, otherwise null.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if source or target towns are not found in the graph.
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if any of the specified towns is null.

      • addVertex

        public boolean addVertex(Town t)
                  throws java.lang.NullPointerException
        Adds the specified town to this graph if not already present. More formally, adds the specified town, t, to this graph if this graph contains no town u such that u.equals(v). If this graph already contains such vertex, the call leaves this graph unchanged and returns false. In combination with the restriction on constructors, this ensures that graphs never contain duplicate town.
        Specified by:
        addVertex in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
        Parameters:
        t - - town to be added to this graph.
        Returns:
        true if this graph did not already contain the specified town.
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if the specified town is null.

      • containsEdge

        public boolean containsEdge(Town sourceVertex,
                            Town destinationVertex)
        Returns true if and only if this graph contains a road going from the source town to the target town. In undirected graphs the same result is obtained when source and target are inverted. If any of the specified towns does not exist in the graph, or if is null, returns false.
        Specified by:
        containsEdge in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
        Parameters:
        sourceVertex - - source town of the road.
        destinationVertex - - target town of the road.
        Returns:

      • containsVertex

        public boolean containsVertex(Town t)
        Returns true if this graph contains the specified town. More formally, returns true if and only if this graph contains a town u such that u.equals(v). If the specified town is null returns false.
        Specified by:
        containsVertex in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>

      • dijkstraShortestPath

        public void dijkstraShortestPath(Town sourceVertex)
        Dijkstra's Shortest Path Method using Adjancency Matrix. Internal structures are built which hold the ability to retrieve the path, shortest distance from the sourceVertex to all the other vertices in the graph, etc.
        Specified by:
        dijkstraShortestPath in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>

      • edgeSet

        public java.util.Set<Road> edgeSet()
        Returns a set of the roads contained in this graph. The set is backed by the graph, so changes to the graph are reflected in the set. If the graph is modified while an iteration over the set is in progress, the results of the iteration are undefined.
        Specified by:
        edgeSet in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
        Returns:
        a set of the roads contained in this graph.

      • removeVertex

        public boolean removeVertex(Town t)
        Removes the specified town from this graph including all its touching roads if present. More formally, if the graph contains a town u such that u.equals(t), the call removes all roads that touch u and then removes u itself. If no such u is found, the call leaves the graph unchanged. Returns true if the graph contained the specified town.
        Specified by:
        removeVertex in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment6.GraphInterface<Town,Road>
        Parameters:
        t - - town to be removed from this graph, if present.
        Returns:
        true if the graph contained the specified vertex; false otherwise.
